(1, 'Martian City Has RCU-Protected Newspaper', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521716250348-c4ae4ff1df43?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2082&q=80', 'burning newspaper', 'The object to be secured',
 '*Statement published by Isotopia''s governor:*

In this city, there is only one version of our single, magnificent newspaper.
How old is the latest accessible version, you ask? Several decades. You see, it''s protected by a RCU lock, meaning that as long as people are constantly accessing the newspaper, old versions won''t be deleted. This has led to severe misunderstandings and, for you, an unfathomable anxiety regarding the validity of our information, but the benefit of actually having the newspaper be accessible by all people with very low latency and only rarely some actual version conflict (people see the date stamp, after all) more than makes up for it.

That''s all I''d like to say.
Welcome to our grand metropolis, visitors.
