(5, 'Apartment Apparatus', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1473893604213-3df9c15611c0?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1951&q=80', 'barren apartment', 'A stone cold & lonely apartment',
 '*The following is a short writeup by an anonymous student that accidentally won a literary price for some other, unrelated work*

So this is a thing that''s being produced and sold? A place where people can stow away their things and occasionally live? A home?

This isn''t a cozy home to return to, it won''t welcome you with open doors and heartwarming surfaces. It''s just an empty shell you can never truly place your identity in, for when you and your things are gone it''ll be filled with another person''s life. The shell stays, the people change. From time to time, they break things - or the things break themselves - that will be replaced by new things that look just the same. All to let this room hold people again. After you''re gone, there might be others here, living their life, stowing their belongings away, using them if so happens, making food and making love, but no love will ever stay here. This place is forever cursed to belong to the next person it is given. Forever, ''till the day it breaks.',
 '2019-09-25 13:13:13', 2, 'culture'),
